  "prompt": "What is love when there is nobody to love?",
  "response": "When there is nobody to love, love can still exist within you as a form of self-love, self-compassion, or an appreciation for the world around you. Love is not exclusively about romantic or interpersonal relationships; it can also be a profound sense of connection to oneself, to nature, to art, or to one's passions and values. It can be a state of being that fosters growth, empathy, and understanding inside oneself. Exploring and nurturing these forms of love can bring meaning and fulfillment, even when there is no immediate person to direct your love toward.",
